== Hong Kong's &quot;Gang of Four&quot; ==
In 2013, Mainland Chinese state media labelled [[Anson Chan]], [[Martin Lee]], [[Joseph Zen]] and [[Jimmy Lai]] as ‘Hong Kong's &quot;Gang of Four&quot;’ due to their alleged foreign connections.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/hkedition/2013-04/26/content_16450955.htm|title=What's Chan up to?|publisher=China Daily|date=2013-04-26|access-date=2019-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190814110426/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/hkedition/2013-04/26/content_16450955.htm|archive-date=2019-08-14|url-status=live}}&lt;/ref&gt;

In 2019, Chinese state media labelled Anson Chan, Martin Lee, Jimmy Lai and [[Albert Ho]] as the gang of four due to their alleged collusion with foreign forces in relation to the [[2019–20 Hong Kong protests]].&lt;ref name=ftgang&gt;{{cite news |title=Hong Kong's 'Gang of Four' hits back at Beijing |url=https://www.ft.com/content/d7e73864-c3b8-11e9-a8e9-296ca66511c9 |publisher=FT |date=August 22, 2019 |quote=Official Chinese Communist party mouthpieces have run editorials over several days labelling the four individuals as Hong Kong’s “Gang of Four”, a chilling reference to four party members who rose to prominence during China’s Cultural Revolution in the 1960s before being charged with treason. |access-date=August 30, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825072013/https://www.ft.com/content/d7e73864-c3b8-11e9-a8e9-296ca66511c9 |archive-date=August 25, 2019 |url-status=live }}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref name=bloomberggang&gt;{{cite news |title=China Compares Hong Kong Democrats to Mao-Era 'Gang of Four' |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-08-19/china-compares-hong-kong-s-democrats-to-mao-era-gang-of-four |agency=Bloomberg |publisher=Bloomberg |date=August 19, 2019 |access-date=August 30, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830080406/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-08-19/china-compares-hong-kong-s-democrats-to-mao-era-gang-of-four |archive-date=August 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}&lt;/ref&gt; The phrase has in turn been denounced by the four individuals.&lt;ref name=ftgang/&gt;

==Popular culture==
English [[post-punk]] band [[Gang of Four (band)|Gang of Four]] are named after the faction.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|last1=Lester|first1=Paul|title=Gang of Four: Damaged Gods|publisher=[[Omnibus Press]]|year=2008|page=24|isbn=978-1-84772-245-4}}&lt;/ref&gt;

